  "description": {
   "en": "The world of Mahjong Gekiga from the 1970s is back here! The fantastic work that was published in Japan's first mahjong manga magazine \"Gamble Punch'' has now been revived as an e-book. A drama depicting the passions of people obsessed with mahjong at a time when mahjong was still considered \"unhealthy\"!\n\"Jean Valjean'' depicts the downfall of a man who cheats once to earn money for his sick wife's hospitalization expenses, and \"Hellborns'' is the story of a monk who breaks the precepts and destroys his opponent by setting up a mahjong match. and \"Lone Wolf'',\na lone sparrow demon who confirms his life at the moment of victory or defeat.\n\nAuthor: Narushima Born in Tokyo in 1940. In 1959, he became Mitsuteru Yokoyama's assistant and made his debut in Shueisha's boy's magazine Hinomaru with the song ``Bangtan Route 3''. He later expanded into a youth magazine and wrote many mahjong comics. He passed away in 2003."
